  "texts": [
    "To assign scores to accounts, we start from source credibility scores, which are domain ratings obtained from NewsGuard in April 2021 for the Twitter_Covid and October 2022 for the Twitter_Midterm and Facebook_Midterm.",
    "We then compute an account score as a weighted mean of the scores of the sources they share.",
    "Note that not all accounts have a score as a result.",
    "Finally, following NewsGuard's rubric, we use a threshold of 60 for labeling accounts with a score below/above 60 as low/high-credibility.",
    "Network description Reshare networkSince reshare information is not included in Facebook data, the reshare network can only be constructed from the two Twitterfoot_1 datasets out of the three datasets considered."
  ],
